<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="273" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1447,1617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1447,1473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Remarks.</emphasis>
This widespread species is known from many countries of the Palaearctic and Oriental regions; among them 
<collectingCountry box="[215,313,1483,1509]" name="Hungary" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Hungary</collectingCountry>
is also listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yu, D. S. &amp; van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K." box="[503,684,1483,1509]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" refId="ref7112" refString="Yu, D. S., van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K. (2016) Taxapad 2016, Ichneumonoidea 2015. Nepean, Ontario. Database on flash-drive. Available from: http: // www. taxapad. com" type="url" year="2016">
Yu 
<emphasis box="[542,592,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, citing 
<bibRefCitation author="Zilahi-Kiss, A." box="[767,979,1483,1509]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" pagination="32 - 146" refId="ref7157" refString="Zilahi-Kiss, A. (1924) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der ungarischen und siebenburgischen Ichneumoniden- (Schlupfwespen-) Fauna. Verhandlungen und Mitteilungen des Siebenburgischen Vereins fur Naturwissenschaften in Hermannstadt, 72 - 74, 32 - 146." type="journal article" year="1924">Zilahi-Kiss (1924)</bibRefCitation>
. However, the voucher specimens of the records in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zilahi-Kiss, A." box="[272,480,1519,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" pagination="32 - 146" refId="ref7157" refString="Zilahi-Kiss, A. (1924) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der ungarischen und siebenburgischen Ichneumoniden- (Schlupfwespen-) Fauna. Verhandlungen und Mitteilungen des Siebenburgischen Vereins fur Naturwissenschaften in Hermannstadt, 72 - 74, 32 - 146." type="journal article" year="1924">Zilahi-Kiss (1924)</bibRefCitation>
were found in HNHM, re-examined, and turned out to be misidentified (all of them are actually 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smits van Burgst" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[288,512,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[288,512,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Cymodusa australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Since no other specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holmgren" authorityYear="1860" box="[858,1107,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennator">
<emphasis box="[858,1107,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Cymodusa antennator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found from 
<collectingCountry box="[1309,1407,1555,1581]" name="Hungary" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Hungary</collectingCountry>
in HNHM, the (highly probable) occurrence of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[818,916,1591,1617]" name="Hungary" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Hungary</collectingCountry>
still awaits confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
